:A.&nbsp;{{note label|MKCity|A|a}}{{note label|MKCity|A|b}}{{note label|MKCity|A|c}} The name "[[Milton Keynes City F.C.|Milton Keynes City]]" refers to two different clubs: the former Bletchley Town F.C., which took the name in 1974 and used it until its liquidation in 1985; and [[Spartan South Midlands League]] side Mercedes-Benz F.C., which renamed itself in 1998 and retained the title until its own demise in 2003.<ref name=mkc/><ref name=goinggoing/><ref name=gone/>
:B.&nbsp;{{note|Wolverton}}[[Wolverton A.F.C.|Wolverton Town & B.R.]] went through a variety of names after the founding of Milton Keynes in 1967, dropping "B.R." in 1981 before adding "(Milton Keynes)" in 1987 to become Wolverton Town (Milton Keynes). A year later the naming order was reversed, with the club now becoming Milton Keynes Wolverton Town, or Milton Keynes Wolves. Finally, in 1990, the name Wolverton A.F.C. was adopted, which remained until the club's dissolution in 1992.<ref name=fchdwtfc/><ref name="fchdwtmk">{{cite web
